#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/vmscape.rst:33
msgid "Mitigation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/vmscape.rst:36
msgid "Conditional IBPB"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/vmscape.rst:38
msgid ""
"Kernel tracks when a CPU has run a potentially malicious guest and issues an "
"IBPB before the first exit to userspace after VM-exit. If userspace did not "
"run between VM-exit and the next VM-entry, no IBPB is issued."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/vmscape.rst:42
msgid ""
"Note that the existing userspace mitigation against Spectre-v2 is effective "
"in protecting the userspace. They are insufficient to protect the userspace "
"VMMs from a malicious guest. This is because Spectre-v2 mitigations are "
"applied at context switch time, while the userspace VMM can run after a VM-"
"exit without a context switch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/vmscape.rst:48
msgid ""
"Vulnerability enumeration and mitigation is not applied inside a guest. This "
"is because nested hypervisors should already be deploying IBPB to isolate "
"themselves from nested guests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/vmscape.rst:53
msgid "SMT considerations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/vmscape.rst:55
msgid ""
"When Simultaneous Multi-Threading (SMT) is enabled, hypervisors can be "
"vulnerable to cross-thread attacks. For complete protection against VMSCAPE "
"attacks in SMT environments, STIBP should be enabled."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/vmscape.rst:59
msgid ""
"The kernel will issue a warning if SMT is enabled without adequate STIBP "
"protection. Warning is not issued when:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/vmscape.rst:62
msgid "SMT is disabled"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/vmscape.rst:63
msgid "STIBP is enabled system-wide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../admin-guide/hw-vuln/vmscape.rst:64
msgid "Intel eIBRS is enabled (which implies STIBP protection)"
msgstr ""

